article.headline: Rice 79, Houston 71
article.story: HOUSTON -- Jarelle Reischel scored 16 points and Tamir Jackson and Connor Frizzelle added 13 each to lead Rice to a 79-71 victory against Houston on Wednesday night. Dylan Ennis had 10 points for the Owls (14-11, 5-5 Conference USA), who outscored Houston 16-7 over the final 5:23. Jonathon Simmons had 16 points and 10 rebounds for the Cougars (11-12, 3-7), and Joseph Young and Alandise Harris scored 13 points apiece. Omar Oraby scored seven points during a 9-0 Rice run that gave it a 72-64 lead with 2:35 remaining. Houston got no closer. The Owls started the game in a hole, as the Cougars scored the first 13 points. Rice fought back to take a 26-25 lead on Reischel's 3-pointer with 3:07 left in the first half, and the teams stayed close until the final minutes. Arsalan Kazemi, Rice's leading scorer and one of the top rebounders (11.0 a game) in the country, was limited to seven points and six boards.
